First we rank aggregate the per-class metrics for F1-score, balanced accuracy and kappa. 2. Then we take the aggregated lists from the three metrics and perform a final rank aggregation. 3. The top workflows from the final rank aggregation are used for gene optimization in the confirmation set ### Across Classes ::: {.cell} ::: ::: {#rank-agg-metrics .panel-tabset .nav-pills} #### F1-Score ::: {#tbl-rank-agg-f1 .cell tbl-cap='F1-Score Rank Aggregation Summary'} ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}

Thus, we cannot piece together the test set predictions from the sequential and two-step algorithms to obtain overall metrics. ## Optimal Gene Sets ### Sequential Algorithm ::: {.cell} ::: {#fig-gene-seq .cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` Gene Optimization for Sequential Classifier ::: ::: In the sequential algorithm, all sequences have relatively flat average F1-scores across the number of genes added.
